Note: ============================================================================
Note: LEXER STRUCTURE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
40-byte lexer record (5 fields x 8 bytes): source pointer, current position,
length, line, column. No nesting/depth counters needed because Kotlin has
no significant-whitespace grammar (unlike Python/F#).
@End Reasoning
Type called "KotlinLexer":
    source as Integer
    position as Integer
    len as Integer
    current_line as Integer
    current_column as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MAIN LEXER FUNCTIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Allocates the 40-byte record and initialises position to 0, line/column
to 1 (1-based for human-readable diagnostics). source_len is cached so
recognisers never re-call string_length per byte.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_kotlin_lexer" takes source_code as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source_len be proc string_length from StringCore with source_code
    Let lexer be proc allocate from Layout with 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0, source_code
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16, source_len
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 24, 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 32, 1
    Return lexer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Main tokeniser dispatch. After skipping whitespace and comments we branch
on the lead character into the matching recogniser. The triple-quoted
multiline string check comes before the regular string check because the
opener ('"""') begins with a quote; checking the single-quote form first
would shadow it.
@End Reasoning
Process called "next_token" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    proc skip_whitespace_and_comments with lexer

    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16

    If pos is greater than or equal to len:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_EOF, pos, pos
    End If

    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos

    Note: Identifiers and keywords
    If proc is_letter with ch is equal to 1:
        Return proc lex_identifier_or_keyword with lexer
    End If

    Note: Numbers
    If proc is_digit with ch is equal to 1:
        Return proc lex_number with lexer
    End If

    Note: Triple-quoted (multiline) string MUST be checked before regular string
    If ch is equal to 34:
        Let next1 be proc peek_char with lexer, 1
        Let next2 be proc peek_char with lexer, 2
        If next1 is equal to 34:
            If next2 is equal to 34:
                Return proc lex_multiline_string with lexer
            End If
        End If
        Return proc lex_string with lexer
    End If

    Note: Character literals
    If ch is equal to 39:
        Return proc lex_char with lexer
    End If

    Note: Operators and punctuation
    Return proc lex_operator_or_punct with lexer
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WHITESPACE AND COMMENT HANDLING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Loop alternating between whitespace and comment skipping; either pass
can expose more of the other (e.g., whitespace after a comment, comment
after whitespace), so we iterate until both quiesce.
@End Reasoning
Process called "skip_whitespace_and_comments" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        proc skip_whitespace with lexer
        Let skipped_comment be proc try_skip_comment with lexer
        If skipped_comment is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Skips space (32), tab (9), LF (10), and CR (13). LF triggers advance_newline
to bump the line counter; the other forms just advance the column. Kotlin
is not significant-whitespace, so consumed whitespace produces no token.
@End Reasoning
Process called "skip_whitespace" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
        If pos is greater than or equal to len:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
        If ch is equal to 32:
            proc advance_position with lexer
        Otherwise:
            If ch is equal to 9:
                proc advance_position with lexer
            Otherwise:
                If ch is equal to 13:
                    proc advance_position with lexer
                Otherwise:
                    If ch is equal to 10:
                        proc advance_newline with lexer
                    Otherwise:
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Tries to consume "//" line comment or "/*...*/" block comment; returns 1
if any was skipped, 0 otherwise. Kotlin block comments nest, so the
recogniser tracks depth rather than scanning for the first "*/".
@End Reasoning
Process called "try_skip_comment" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16

    If pos is greater than or equal to len:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
    If ch is not equal to 47:
        Return 0
    End If

    If pos plus 1 is greater than or equal to len:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let next_ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos plus 1

    Note: Line comment //
    If next_ch is equal to 47:
        proc advance_position with lexer
        proc advance_position with lexer
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let p be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
            If p is greater than or equal to len:
                Return 1
            End If
            Let c be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, p
            If c is equal to 10:
                Return 1
            End If
            proc advance_position with lexer
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Block comment /* ... */ (nesting-aware)
    If next_ch is equal to 42:
        proc advance_position with lexer
        proc advance_position with lexer
        Let depth be 1
        While depth is greater than 0:
            Let p be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
            If p is greater than or equal to len:
                Return 1
            End If
            Let c be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, p
            Let c2 be 0
            If p plus 1 is less than len:
                Set c2 to proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, p plus 1
            End If
            If c is equal to 47:
                If c2 is equal to 42:
                    proc advance_position with lexer
                    proc advance_position with lexer
                    Set depth to depth plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    proc advance_position with lexer
                End If
            Otherwise:
                If c is equal to 42:
                    If c2 is equal to 47:
                        proc advance_position with lexer
                        proc advance_position with lexer
                        Set depth to depth minus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        proc advance_position with lexer
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    If c is equal to 10:
                        proc advance_newline with lexer
                    Otherwise:
                        proc advance_position with lexer
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End While
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: IDENTIFIER AND KEYWORD LEXING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Reads identifier characters (letters, digits, underscore) then runs
match_kotlin_keyword. If the lexeme matches a keyword, returns the
keyword token; otherwise returns TOKEN_IDENTIFIER. The scan always
advances at least one character (the lead is already a letter), so the
enclosing token loop can never spin.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lex_identifier_or_keyword" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let start_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let pos be start_pos

    While pos is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
        Let is_id_char be proc is_identifier_char with ch
        If is_id_char is equal to 0:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Let keyword_type be proc match_kotlin_keyword with source, start_pos, pos
            If keyword_type is not equal to 0:
                Return proc create_token with keyword_type, start_pos, pos
            End If
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, start_pos, pos
        End If
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
    Let keyword_type2 be proc match_kotlin_keyword with source, start_pos, pos
    If keyword_type2 is not equal to 0:
        Return proc create_token with keyword_type2, start_pos, pos
    End If
    Return proc create_token with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, start_pos, pos
End Process

@Reasoning:
Keyword matcher: extracts the lexeme then compares against the full Kotlin
soft/hard keyword set. Returns 0 (not a keyword) when no candidate matches,
which lex_identifier_or_keyword treats as an ordinary identifier. Note that
Kotlin "soft" keywords (data, sealed, open, get, set, etc.) are only keywords
in specific positions; tokenising them as keyword tokens and letting the parser
treat unexpected keyword tokens as identifiers in expression position keeps the
lexer simple while remaining correct.
@End Reasoning
Process called "kotlin_substring" takes source as Integer, start_pos as Integer, end_pos as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Copy source bytes [start_pos, end_pos) into a new NUL-terminated string.
    Let len be end_pos minus start_pos
    If len is less than 0:
        Set len to 0
    End If
    Let buffer be proc allocate from Layout with len plus 1
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with source, start_pos plus i
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, i, ch
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, len, 0
    Return buffer
End Process

Process called "match_kotlin_keyword" takes source as Integer, start as Integer, end_pos as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc kotlin_substring with source, start, end_pos

    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "if" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_IF
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "else" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_ELSE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "when" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_WHEN
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "for" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_FOR
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "while" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_WHILE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "do" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_DO
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "return" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_RETURN
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "break" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_BREAK
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "continue" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_CONTINUE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "package" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_PACKAGE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "import" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_IMPORT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "fun" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_FUN
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "val" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_VAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "var" is equal to 1:
        Return TOKEN_VAR
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with text, "class" is equal to 1:
