Note: ============================================================================
Note: NUMBER LEXING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Kotlin number literals support decimal, hex (0x), binary (0b), and underscore
digit separators. Suffixes (L for Long, F/f for Float, u/U for unsigned)
are parsed at the end and select the precise integer/float token kind.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lex_number" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let start_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let pos be start_pos

    Let is_hex be 0
    Let is_binary be 0
    Let is_float be 0
    Let is_long be 0

    Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
    If ch is equal to 48:
        If pos plus 1 is less than len:
            Let next_ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos plus 1
            If next_ch is equal to 120:
                Set is_hex to 1
                Set pos to pos plus 2
            End If
            If next_ch is equal to 88:
                Set is_hex to 1
                Set pos to pos plus 2
            End If
            If next_ch is equal to 98:
                Set is_binary to 1
                Set pos to pos plus 2
            End If
            If next_ch is equal to 66:
                Set is_binary to 1
                Set pos to pos plus 2
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If pos is greater than or equal to len:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
            If ch is equal to 95:
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Let is_valid be 0
                If is_hex is equal to 1:
                    Set is_valid to proc is_hex_digit with ch
                Otherwise:
                    If is_binary is equal to 1:
                        If ch is equal to 48:
                            Set is_valid to 1
                        End If
                        If ch is equal to 49:
                            Set is_valid to 1
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        Set is_valid to proc is_digit with ch
                    End If
                End If

                If is_valid is equal to 1:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    If ch is equal to 46:
                        Note: Only treat '.' as a decimal point if followed by a digit
                        Note: (avoids consuming the range operator '..').
                        Let after be 0
                        If pos plus 1 is less than len:
                            Set after to proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos plus 1
                        End If
                        If proc is_digit with after is equal to 1:
                            Set is_float to 1
                            Set pos to pos plus 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Set scanning to 0
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        If ch is equal to 101:
                            Set is_float to 1
                            Set pos to pos plus 1
                            If pos is less than len:
                                Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
                                If ch is equal to 43:
                                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                                End If
                                If ch is equal to 45:
                                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                                End If
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            Set scanning to 0
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Note: Type suffix
    If pos is less than len:
        Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
        If ch is equal to 76:
            Set is_long to 1
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        Otherwise:
            If ch is equal to 102:
                Set is_float to 1
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            Otherwise:
                If ch is equal to 70:
                    Set is_float to 1
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    If ch is equal to 117:
                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                        If pos is less than len:
                            Let su be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
                            If su is equal to 76:
                                Set is_long to 1
                                Set pos to pos plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        If ch is equal to 85:
                            Set pos to pos plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos

    If is_long is equal to 1:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_LONG_LITERAL, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If is_float is equal to 1:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_FLOAT_LITERAL, start_pos, pos
    End If
    Return proc create_token with TOKEN_INTEGER_LITERAL, start_pos, pos
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: STRING AND CHARACTER LEXING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Regular Kotlin string "..." with escape sequences (\n, \t, \", \$, etc.)
and string interpolation ($var, ${expr}). Interpolation is preserved as
part of the lexeme; the parser treats the whole thing as a string literal.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lex_string" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let start_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let pos be start_pos plus 1

    While pos is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
        If ch is equal to 34:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_STRING_LITERAL, start_pos, pos
        End If
        If ch is equal to 92:
            Set pos to pos plus 2
        Otherwise:
            If ch is equal to 10:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
                Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ERROR, start_pos, pos
            Otherwise:
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
    Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ERROR, start_pos, pos
End Process

@Reasoning:
Triple-quoted Kotlin string """...""": preserves embedded newlines and
disables backslash escapes (raw form), but still supports $-interpolation.
Closing delimiter is the next standalone """ sequence.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lex_multiline_string" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let start_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let pos be start_pos plus 3

    While pos is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
        If ch is equal to 34:
            If pos plus 2 is less than len:
                Let next1 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos plus 1
                Let next2 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos plus 2
                If next1 is equal to 34:
                    If next2 is equal to 34:
                        Set pos to pos plus 3
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
                        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_MULTILINE_STRING, start_pos, pos
                    End If
                End If
            Otherwise:
                If pos plus 2 is equal to len minus 1:
                    Note: handled below by EOF fallthrough
                    Set pos to pos
                End If
            End If
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
    Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ERROR, start_pos, pos
End Process

@Reasoning:
Kotlin Char literal 'X' with single character or escape sequence. Distinct
from Java/C++ char literals because Kotlin Char is 16-bit (Unicode BMP).
Unterminated literals return TOKEN_ERROR.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lex_char" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let start_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let pos be start_pos plus 1

    If pos is greater than or equal to len:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ERROR, start_pos, pos
    End If

    Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
    If ch is equal to 92:
        Set pos to pos plus 2
    Otherwise:
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If

    If pos is less than len:
        Set ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
        If ch is equal to 39:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_CHAR_LITERAL, start_pos, pos
        End If
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
    Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ERROR, start_pos, pos
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: OPERATOR AND PUNCTUATION LEXING
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Operator/punctuation recogniser. Kotlin has many multi-character operators
(===, !==, ==, !=, ?:, ?., !!, ::, ->, .., ++, --, +=, etc.) so we maximally
munch by peeking ahead one or two characters before committing to a shorter
match. The single lead character is always consumed, so the token loop never
stalls even on an unrecognised byte (which returns TOKEN_ERROR after one
advance).
@End Reasoning
Process called "lex_operator_or_punct" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let start_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let pos be start_pos

    Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
    Set pos to pos plus 1

    Let next_ch be 0
    Let next2_ch be 0
    If pos is less than len:
        Set next_ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos
    End If
    If pos plus 1 is less than len:
        Set next2_ch to proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, pos plus 1
    End If

    Note: Three-character operators === and !==
    If ch is equal to 61:
        If next_ch is equal to 61:
            If next2_ch is equal to 61:
                Set pos to pos plus 2
                proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
                Return proc create_token with TOKEN_EQUAL_REF, start_pos, pos
            End If
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_EQUAL, start_pos, pos
        End If
    End If

    If ch is equal to 33:
        If next_ch is equal to 61:
            If next2_ch is equal to 61:
                Set pos to pos plus 2
                proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
                Return proc create_token with TOKEN_NOT_EQUAL_REF, start_pos, pos
            End If
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_NOT_EQUAL, start_pos, pos
        End If
        If next_ch is equal to 33:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_NOT_NULL, start_pos, pos
        End If
    End If

    If ch is equal to 63:
        If next_ch is equal to 58:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ELVIS, start_pos, pos
        End If
        If next_ch is equal to 46:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_SAFE_CALL, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_QUESTION, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 45:
        If next_ch is equal to 62:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ARROW, start_pos, pos
        End If
        If next_ch is equal to 61:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_MINUS_ASSIGN, start_pos, pos
        End If
        If next_ch is equal to 45:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_DECREMENT, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_MINUS, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 58:
        If next_ch is equal to 58:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_DOUBLE_COLON, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_COLON, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 46:
        If next_ch is equal to 46:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_RANGE, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_DOT, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 43:
        If next_ch is equal to 61:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_PLUS_ASSIGN, start_pos, pos
        End If
        If next_ch is equal to 43:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_INCREMENT, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_PLUS, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 42:
        If next_ch is equal to 61:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_STAR_ASSIGN, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_STAR, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 47:
        If next_ch is equal to 61:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_SLASH_ASSIGN, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_SLASH, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 37:
        If next_ch is equal to 61:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_PERCENT_ASSIGN, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_PERCENT, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 61:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ASSIGN, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 60:
        If next_ch is equal to 61:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_LESS_EQUAL, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_LESS, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 62:
        If next_ch is equal to 61:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_GREATER_EQUAL, start_pos, pos
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_GREATER, start_pos, pos
    End If

    If ch is equal to 38:
        If next_ch is equal to 38:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_AND, start_pos, pos
        End If
    End If

    If ch is equal to 124:
        If next_ch is equal to 124:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos
            Return proc create_token with TOKEN_OR, start_pos, pos
        End If
    End If

    Note: Single-character operators and punctuation
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos

    If ch is equal to 33:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_NOT, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If ch is equal to 40:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_LPAREN, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If ch is equal to 41:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_RPAREN, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If ch is equal to 123:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_LBRACE, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If ch is equal to 125:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_RBRACE, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If ch is equal to 91:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_LBRACKET, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If ch is equal to 93:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_RBRACKET, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If ch is equal to 59:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_SEMICOLON, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If ch is equal to 44:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_COMMA, start_pos, pos
    End If
    If ch is equal to 64:
        Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ANNOTATION_USE, start_pos, pos
    End If

    Return proc create_token with TOKEN_ERROR, start_pos, pos
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HELPER FUNCTIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
ASCII letter or underscore. Kotlin identifiers in source are practically
ASCII (backtick-quoted identifiers can be arbitrary, handled separately).
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_letter" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    If ch is greater than or equal to 65:
        If ch is less than or equal to 90:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than or equal to 97:
        If ch is less than or equal to 122:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is equal to 95:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
ASCII 0-9 classifier. Used for the leading character of number literals
and as part of identifier continuation characters.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_digit" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    If ch is greater than or equal to 48:
        If ch is less than or equal to 57:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Hex digit (0-9, A-F, a-f) classifier. Used inside the hex-prefix (0x)
branch of lex_number.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_hex_digit" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc is_digit with ch is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If ch is greater than or equal to 65:
        If ch is less than or equal to 70:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than or equal to 97:
        If ch is less than or equal to 102:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Identifier-continuation classifier: letter, digit, or underscore. Used
by lex_identifier_or_keyword for second-and-later characters.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_identifier_char" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    Let is_letter_val be proc is_letter with ch
    If is_letter_val is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let is_digit_val be proc is_digit with ch
    If is_digit_val is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lookahead helper that does not advance the cursor. Returns the byte at
position+offset or 0 at EOF, used to disambiguate multi-character operators.
@End Reasoning
Process called "peek_char" takes lexer as Integer, offset as Integer returns Integer:
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 0
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 16
    Let peek_pos be pos plus offset
    If peek_pos is greater than or equal to len:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc string_char_at from StringCore with source, peek_pos
End Process

@Reasoning:
Advances position by 1 and increments column (no line bump). Field offsets:
position@8, current_column@32.
@End Reasoning
Process called "advance_position" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let col be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 32
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 32, col plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Advances position past a newline: increments line (offset 24), resets column
(offset 32) to 1.
@End Reasoning
Process called "advance_newline" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8
    Let line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with lexer, 24
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 8, pos plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 24, line plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with lexer, 32, 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Allocates and initialises a Token record. Stores the token kind plus the
source-range [start, end_pos) so subsequent passes extract the lexeme
without re-walking the source. Three 8-byte fields = 24 bytes.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_token" takes token_type as Integer, start as Integer, end_pos as Integer returns Integer:
    Let token be proc allocate from Layout with 24
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with token, 0, token_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with token, 8, start
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with token, 16, end_pos
    Return token
End Process

@Reasoning:
Token record carrying the kind and source range [start, end_pos).
@End Reasoning
Type called "Token":
    type as Integer
    start_pos as Integer
    end_pos as Integer
End Type
